| Syncing Music Players In Linux?                                    |
|   from the keeping-it-consistent dept.                             |
|   posted by kdawson on Thursday May 31, @10:41 (GNOME)             |
|   http://ask.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/31/1327204          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Daengbo writes "I recently sold my old laptop to a friend, and she
asked me to keep Ubuntu on it rather than installing Windows for her. To
help her with the transition, I wrote two [1]intro [2]lessons for her,
but we've hit a stumbling block. The iRivier Clix (4GB) she's been using
syncs with Windows Media Player. My research shows that the model has
both an MTP for the sync and a UMS mode which acts as a mass storage
device. Rhythmbox's 'Scan Removable Media' doesn't pick up anything from
the USB mass storage device, and although [3]Syncropated claims to
support these types of devices, it doesn't find any supported devices.
Unless you use an iPod, this appears to be a real weak point in the Linux
desktop. Do you sync your mass storage devices and music players? What do
you use?"

