    1. http://arstechnica.com/news.ars/post/20070530-windows-vista-no-more-secure-than-xp-report.html


+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| City Almost Loses 450K to Keylogger                                |
|   from the never-too-safe dept.                                    |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Thursday May 31, @19:31 (Security)       |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/31/2236236           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]SierraPete writes "The city of Carson, California (a suburb of Los
Angeles) was the target of a 6-digit theft of cash. The LA Times reports
that information taken from a keylogger was [1]used to attempt to steal
$450K from the city's treasury. Quick work by the city froze most of the
funds, but it drives home the importance of keeping good anti-spyware and
anti-virus software updated on both corporate systems as well as systems
being used from home."

